UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2439
1 AN ACT relating to health services.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 211.160 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) The secretary for health and family services may, from the funds available, employ,
5 by contract or otherwise such medical, clinical, technical, and other personnel that
6 he or she deems necessary to effectuate the purposes of KRS 211.130 to 211.160,
7 and fix and pay their compensation and necessary traveling expenses.
8 (2) The secretary for health and family services may, from the funds available, procure,
9 by purchase or lease or otherwise, such property, equipment, services, facilities, and
10 supplies that he or she deems necessary to effectuate the purposes of KRS 211.130
11 to 211.160.
12 (3) The secretary for health and family services is authorized to accept, on behalf of the
13 Commonwealth of Kentucky, all gifts, donations, contributions, grants, devises,
14 bequests, and conveyances of real and personal property for establishing, providing,
15 and maintaining the services and facilities described in KRS 211.150, subject only
16 to the condition that same shall be devoted to and used for said purposes. All funds
17 received by the secretary for health and family services shall be deposited in the
18 State Treasury and credited to a trust and agency fund account and expended only
19 for purposes authorized by KRS 211.130 to 211.160.
20 (4) The secretary for health and family services may make and issue all necessary rules
21 and regulations to carry out KRS 211.130 to 211.160; provided, however, that no
22 educable person shall be eligible for any benefits hereunder unless he or she is, and
23 has been continuously for at least twelve (12) months immediately preceding the
24 date of his or her application therefor, an actual resident of this state.
25 (5) The secretary for health and family services may delegate to any division of the
26 cabinet, or to any director thereof, any and all of his or her authority and duties
27 hereunder.
