1 (6) Upon request of the secretary for health and family services, approved in writing by
2 the Governor, any cabinet, agency, or commission of the Commonwealth shall
3 furnish without cost to the cabinet such services, facilities, and assistance as are
4 available and, in the judgment of the secretary for health and family services and
5 the Governor, required, to effectuate the purposes of KRS 211.130 to 211.160 or its
6 administration which is hereby vested in the cabinet.
